        {
          "anchor" : "Equation-from-points",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Equation from points",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Assuming you have a Desmos table of points, the column of X values being ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "x1",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and y being ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "y1",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", you can use ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "~",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " instead of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "=",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "use linear regression to determine some unknowns. Remember that it takes two points for a line, and three points for",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "a quadratic.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
